<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Hmmm</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Benign">Benign</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:56 p.m. 8/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Hmmm<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2166" TARGET=_self>Answers for naked rampaging mages</A> (TheBlack)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> First solution is to make it so you come back from death with no

<BR>&gt; mana. I've already asked Brad to put this in on Rallos Zek.
<P>I truly hate this idea. Re-Memming after death is lame enough as is. Takes long enough to med to full right now(Lvl 20) after a battle I win. If I have to mem AND med everytime I die to some creature(or Player) I will start getting pissed off real quick. A fighter and mage with root could put a serious hurting on some manaless spellless mage.
<P>&gt; The second solution is a bit more involved. Mages could be
<BR>&gt; required to purchase magical items, call them foci, that are
<BR>&gt; required for charging mana. Without one you could limit the
<BR>&gt; amount of total mana to 50% of maximum. A lesser foci might give
<BR>&gt; you 80%, a regular 100%, and a powerful quest foci perhaps 110%
<BR>&gt; or more. These foci could take the fom of just about anything (a
<BR>&gt; magical gem for example), but they should be lootable. To make
<BR>&gt; them lootable we could require they remain in one's inventory
<BR>&gt; and be non-equippable, and change looting rules so that only
<BR>&gt; items in the inventory can be looted. The cost of replacing a
<BR>&gt; foci should be similar to what a warrior pays for a decent
<BR>&gt; weapon or a small piece of armor.
<P>Make the wizzies have something that costs the same as a decent warrior weapon and then disallow the looting of warrior weapons? Seems you are turning this completely around. If there were some item spellcasters needed to cast, then all items should be lootable on all people don't you think? You are worried mages will bag this before the looting can begin? Warriors can do that now too.
<P>&gt; Another way to place a foci would be to require it be eqiupped
<BR>&gt; by use of a spell. To unequip it would also require the use of a
<BR>&gt; slow to cast high-mana use spell. In this fashion the item would
<BR>&gt; most likely be equipped at the time of the mage's death.
<P>Plz, no more tedious crap need be added to this game. Balance between tedious and fun is pretty good right now.
<P>I do believe all items on a corpse should be able to be looted(even in a bag). Naked mages have been running rampant in a few places I have frequented lately. It is a shame, but I believe the problem is that there is no XP loss for death from PCs. If someone is known as a PK, he will have enough enemies to make his life rather difficult. As for the fear of bind point killing, I have never seen this done(besides newbie PKs at their starting res point and they dont lose XP anyways) and I believe you should just be careful where you bind. Bind by a guard that likes you if you are that afraid of it happening.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
